data.title: Calligraphy Yang Xin
data.meta_description: Calligraphy Yang Xin - Download as a PDF or view online for free
data.text: The document discusses the history of Chinese calligraphy from its earliest origins in oracle bone script over 8,000 years ago to modern calligraphy styles. It covers the development of characters over time, materials like ink and paper, and different scripts including clerical, regular, semi-cursive and cursive scripts. It also describes a lecture and calligraphy demonstration by Professor Yang Xin of Beijing University on the techniques and expressive aspects of the art form.
